🇸 🇬 🦇 Singapore26-year-old lion city owner suspect charged with murder in Xinshan youth club31/10/2023 16:05Fu Yiming  26  was charged with murder.The 26-year-old Singaporean principal suspect was formally charged with murder today (31) in the case of being assassinated outside a youth nightclub in Xinshan. In addition  he was charged with one count of drug abuse.Fu Yiming  26  was taken to Xinshan Court this morning for prosecution  the China Daily reported. The first charge alleges that he committed murder by killing Xie Zhiyu  a 25-year-old Chinese man  on Road 3 in Sutela  Dafeng Garden  from 3: 00 a.m. to 03:30 on the 27th of this month.The second charge alleges that at 06:05 on the 27th of this month  he was found to contain methamphetamine in the antidrug unit of Xinshan County Police headquarters  violating the drug law  which he denied in court.Under the local decree  once convicted of murder  the defendant will be sentenced to death  and if he has escaped the death penalty  he will face 30 to 40 years in prison and more than 12 lashes.The murder occurred at about 03:41 on the 27th of this month in front of a unit in Xinshan District. A 25-year-old local man was stabbed to death by several men with sharp weapons.Initial investigation showed that the victim had nine wounds in the body  including stab wounds to the right chest  left abdomen  lower left ribs  left shoulder  right back and left back  one wound to the left thumb  one left middle finger and one wound to the left cheek.Two hours after the murder  officers of the District Criminal investigation Unit of San Shan South Police  on the basis of clues  found three suspected persons and a Singapore-registered Audi car in the vicinity of Dundun Buttili Road in San Shan at about 05:30 on the same day.When the police tried to intercept and investigate the car  the driver immediately accelerated his escape and ran out of control in front of the San Shan University Palace. Police subsequently arrested three suspects.
